reviewText: Cranko may not have been a choreographer on the level of Balanchine or Ashton, but this is a lovely memento of his early work, and it's splendid to be reminded of the young Beriosova who shone during the Royal Ballet's first New York performances in the late 40s.  The ballets are little more than jeux d'esprit, but for nostalgic balletomanes of a certain age, they are a treat.
